Japan’s Miki Ando Wins Second Women’s World Figure Skating Title

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-04-30T13:54:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-30/japan-s-miki-ando-wins-second-women-s-world-figure-skating-championship.html
Japan ’s Miki Ando won the women’s
gold medal at the world figure skating championships for her
second world title.  Ando, 23, entered today’s free skate in second place behind
Olympic champion Kim Yuna of  South Korea , who took the silver
medal. Italy’s Carolina Kostner finished third, with defending
champion Mao Asada of Japan sixth. Ando captured her first world
title in 2007.  The championships were originally scheduled to be held in
Tokyo last month and were moved to Moscow following the
earthquake and tsunami in Japan.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  